The recently passed Senate bank bill,which called for a one-year freeze on new bank services andbarred the creation of limited service banks, could hamperforeign banks' operations here, said Lawrence Uhlick, incomingexecutive director of the Institute of Foreign Bankers Inc.    "The language is very unclear and very troublesome," hetold a press briefing.    He said the institute, which represents 230 internationalbanks operating in the U.S., would lobby for changes in thefinal version of the bank bill, which still has to go throughthe House and the conference process before becoming law. Reuter&#3;